EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName IN ("*\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\AMSI\\Providers\\*", "*\\SOFTWARE\\WOW6432Node\\Microsoft\\AMSI\\Providers\\*") NOT ((ProcessName IN ("C:\\Program Files\\Avast Software\\Avast\\RegSvr.exe", "C:\\Program Files\\Avast Software\\Avast\\x86\\RegSvr.exe") ObjectName="*\\{FB904E4E-D2C7-4C8D-8492-B620BB9896B1}*") OR (ProcessName IN ("C:\\Program Files\\AVG\\Antivirus\\RegSvr.exe", "C:\\Program Files\\AVG\\Antivirus\\x86\\RegSvr.exe") ObjectName="*\\{FB904E4E-D2C7-4C8D-8492-B620BB9896B1}*") OR (ProcessName="C:\\Program Files\\Avira\\Endpoint Protection SDK\\endpointprotection.exe" ObjectName="*\\{00000001-3DCC-4B48-A82E-E2071FE58E05}*"))

# ── Potential Persistence Via AppCompat RegisterAppRestart Layer ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Chi tiết: Detects the setting of the REGISTERAPPRESTART compatibility layer on an application. This compatibility layer allows an application to register for restart using the "RegisterApplicationRestart" API. 
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\AppCompatFlags\\Layers\\*" NewValue="*REGISTERAPPRESTART*"

# ── Potential Persistence Via App Paths Default Property ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects changes to the "Default" property for keys located in the \Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\App Paths\ registry. Which might be used as a method of persistence The entries found under
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\App Paths*" ObjectName IN ("*(Default)", "*Path") NewValue IN ("*\\Users\\Public*", "*\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\*", "*\\Windows\\Temp\\*", "*\\Desktop\\*", "*\\Downloads\\*", "*%temp%*", "*%tmp%*", "*iex*", "*Invoke-*", "*rundll32*", "*regsvr32*", "*mshta*", "*cscript*", "*wscript*", "*.bat*", "*.hta*", "*.dll*", "*.ps1*")

# ── Potential Persistence Using DebugPath ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Chi tiết: Detects potential persistence using Appx DebugPath
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" (ObjectName="*Classes\\ActivatableClasses\\Package\\Microsoft.*" ObjectName="*\\DebugPath") OR (ObjectName="*\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\PackagedAppXDebug\\Microsoft.*" ObjectName="*\\(Default)")

# ── Potential Persistence Via AutodialDLL ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects change the the "AutodialDLL" key which could be used as a persistence method to load custom DLL via the "ws2_32" library
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Services\\WinSock2\\Parameters\\AutodialDLL*"

# ── Potential Persistence Via CHM Helper DLL ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects when an attacker modifies the registry key "HtmlHelp Author" to achieve persistence
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName IN ("*\\Software\\Microsoft\\HtmlHelp Author\\Location*", "*\\Software\\WOW6432Node\\Microsoft\\HtmlHelp Author\\Location*")

# ── COM Object Hijacking Via Modification Of Default System CLSID Default Value ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects potential COM object hijacking via modification of default system CLSID.
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\CLSID\\*" ObjectName IN ("*\\InprocServer32\\(Default)", "*\\LocalServer32\\(Default)") ObjectName IN ("*\\{1f486a52-3cb1-48fd-8f50-b8dc300d9f9d}\\*", "*\\{2155fee3-2419-4373-b102-6843707eb41f}\\*", "*\\{4590f811-1d3a-11d0-891f-00aa004b2e24}\\*", "*\\{4de225bf-cf59-4cfc-85f7-68b90f185355}\\*", "*\\{ddc05a5a-351a-4e06-8eaf-54ec1bc2dcea}\\*", "*\\{F56F6FDD-AA9D-4618-A949-C1B91AF43B1A}\\*", "*\\{F82B4EF1-93A9-4DDE-8015-F7950A1A6E31}\\*", "*\\{7849596a-48ea-486e-8937-a2a3009f31a9}\\*", "*\\{0b91a74b-ad7c-4a9d-b563-29eef9167172}\\*", "*\\{603D3801-BD81-11d0-A3A5-00C04FD706EC}\\*", "*\\{30D49246-D217-465F-B00B-AC9DDD652EB7}\\*", "*\\{A7A63E5C-3877-4840-8727-C1EA9D7A4D50}\\*", "*\\{2227A280-3AEA-1069-A2DE-08002B30309D}\\*", "*\\{2DEA658F-54C1-4227-AF9B-260AB5FC3543}\\*", "*\\{AA509086-5Ca9-4C25-8F95-589D3C07B48A}\\*") NewValue IN ("*:\\Perflogs\\*", "*\\AppData\\Local\\*", "*\\Desktop\\*", "*\\Downloads\\*", "*\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Start Menu\\Programs\\Startup\\*", "*\\System32\\spool\\drivers\\color\\*", "*\\Temporary Internet*", "*\\Users\\Public\\*", "*\\Windows\\Temp\\*", "*%appdata%*", "*%temp%*", "*%tmp%*") OR (NewValue="*:\\Users\\*" NewValue="*\\Favorites\\*") OR (NewValue="*:\\Users\\*" NewValue="*\\Favourites\\*") OR (NewValue="*:\\Users\\*" NewValue="*\\Contacts\\*") OR (NewValue="*:\\Users\\*" NewValue="*\\Pictures\\*")

# ── Potential COM Object Hijacking Via TreatAs Subkey - Registry ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Chi tiết: Detects COM object hijacking via TreatAs subkey
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\REGISTRY\\USER\\*" ObjectName="*Classes\\CLSID\\*" ObjectName="*\\TreatAs*" NOT ProcessName="C:\\WINDOWS\\system32\\svchost.exe"

# ── Potential PSFactoryBuffer COM Hijacking ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects changes to the PSFactory COM InProcServer32 registry. This technique was used by RomCom to create persistence storing a malicious DLL.
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\CLSID\\{c90250f3-4d7d-4991-9b69-a5c5bc1c2ae6}\\InProcServer32\\(Default)" NOT (NewValue IN ("%windir%\\System32\\ActXPrxy.dll", "C:\\Windows\\System32\\ActXPrxy.dll"))

# ── Potential Persistence Via Custom Protocol Handler ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Mục đích: Sửa registry
# Chi tiết: Detects potential persistence activity via the registering of a new custom protocole handlers. While legitimate applications register protocole handlers often times during installation. And attacker c
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="HKCR\\*" NewValue="URL:*" NOT (NewValue="URL:ms-*" OR ProcessName IN ("C:\\Program Files (x86)*", "C:\\Program Files\\*", "C:\\Windows\\System32\\*", "C:\\Windows\\SysWOW64\\*"))

# ── Potential Persistence Via Event Viewer Events.asp ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Mục đích: Sửa registry
# Chi tiết: Detects potential registry persistence technique using the Event Viewer "Events.asp" technique
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName IN ("*\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Event Viewer\\MicrosoftRedirectionProgram*", "*\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Event Viewer\\MicrosoftRedirectionURL*") NOT ((ProcessName="*C:\\WINDOWS\\system32\\svchost.exe" ObjectName="*\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Event Viewer\\MicrosoftRedirectionProgram" NewValue="%%SystemRoot%%\\PCHealth\\HelpCtr\\Binaries\\HelpCtr.exe") OR (ProcessName="*C:\\WINDOWS\\system32\\svchost.exe" ObjectName="*\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Event Viewer\\MicrosoftRedirectionProgramCommandLineParameters" NewValue="-url hcp://services/centers/support*topic=%%s") OR NewValue="http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/events.asp" OR NewValue="(Empty)")

# ── Potential Persistence Via GlobalFlags ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects registry persistence technique using the GlobalFlags and SilentProcessExit keys
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" (ObjectName="*\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\*" ObjectName="*\\Image File Execution Options\\*" ObjectName="*\\GlobalFlag*") OR (ObjectName="*\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\*" ObjectName="*\\SilentProcessExit\\*" ObjectName IN ("*\\ReportingMode*", "*\\MonitorProcess*"))

# ── Modification of IE Registry Settings ──
# Mức độ  : Thấp
# Mục đích: Sửa registry
# Chi tiết: Detects modification of the registry settings used for Internet Explorer and other Windows components that use these settings. An attacker can abuse this registry key to add a domain to the trusted si
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings*" NOT (NewValue="DWORD*" OR NOT NewValue=* OR NewValue IN ("Cookie:", "Visited:", "(Empty)") OR ObjectName IN ("*\\Cache*", "*\\ZoneMap*", "*\\WpadDecision*") OR NewValue="Binary Data") NOT ObjectName="*\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Accepted Documents*"

# ── Register New IFiltre For Persistence ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Chi tiết: Detects when an attacker registers a new IFilter for an extension. Microsoft Windows Search uses filters to extract the content of items for inclusion in a full-text index. You can extend Windows Sear
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" (ObjectName="*\\SOFTWARE\\Classes\\.*" ObjectName="*\\PersistentHandler*") OR (ObjectName="*\\SOFTWARE\\Classes\\CLSID*" ObjectName="*\\PersistentAddinsRegistered\\{89BCB740-6119-101A-BCB7-00DD010655AF}*") NOT (ObjectName IN ("*\\CLSID\\{4F46F75F-199F-4C63-8B7D-86D48FE7970C}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{4887767F-7ADC-4983-B576-88FB643D6F79}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{D3B41FA1-01E3-49AF-AA25-1D0D824275AE}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{72773E1A-B711-4d8d-81FA-B9A43B0650DD}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{098f2470-bae0-11cd-b579-08002b30bfeb}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{1AA9BF05-9A97-48c1-BA28-D9DCE795E93C}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{2e2294a9-50d7-4fe7-a09f-e6492e185884}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{34CEAC8D-CBC0-4f77-B7B1-8A60CB6DA0F7}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{3B224B11-9363-407e-850F-C9E1FFACD8FB}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{3DDEB7A4-8ABF-4D82-B9EE-E1F4552E95BE}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{5645C8C1-E277-11CF-8FDA-00AA00A14F93}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{5645C8C4-E277-11CF-8FDA-00AA00A14F93}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{58A9EBF6-5755-4554-A67E-A2467AD1447B}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{5e941d80-bf96-11cd-b579-08002b30bfeb}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{698A4FFC-63A3-4E70-8F00-376AD29363FB}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{7E9D8D44-6926-426F-AA2B-217A819A5CCE}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{8CD34779-9F10-4f9b-ADFB-B3FAEABDAB5A}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{9694E38A-E081-46ac-99A0-8743C909ACB6}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{98de59a0-d175-11cd-a7bd-00006b827d94}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{AA10385A-F5AA-4EFF-B3DF-71B701E25E18}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{B4132098-7A03-423D-9463-163CB07C151F}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{d044309b-5da6-4633-b085-4ed02522e5a5}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{D169C14A-5148-4322-92C8-754FC9D018D8}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{DD75716E-B42E-4978-BB60-1497B92E30C4}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{E2F83EED-62DE-4A9F-9CD0-A1D40DCD13B6}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{E772CEB3-E203-4828-ADF1-765713D981B8}\\*", "*\\CLSID\\{eec97550-47a9-11cf-b952-00aa0051fe20}*", "*\\CLSID\\{FB10BD80-A331-4e9e-9EB7-00279903AD99}\\*") OR ProcessName IN ("C:\\Windows\\System32\\*", "C:\\Program Files (x86)\\*", "C:\\Program Files\\*"))

# ── Potential Persistence Via Logon Scripts - Registry ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Chi tiết: Detects creation of "UserInitMprLogonScript" registry value which can be used as a persistence method by malicious actors
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*UserInitMprLogonScript*"

# ── Potential Persistence Via LSA Extensions ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects when an attacker modifies the "REG_MULTI_SZ" value named "Extensions" to include a custom DLL to achieve persistence via lsass. The "Extensions" list contains filenames of DLLs being automatic
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LsaExtensionConfig\\LsaSrv\\Extensions*"

# ── Potential Persistence Via Mpnotify ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects when an attacker register a new SIP provider for persistence and defense evasion
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\mpnotify*"

# ── Potential Persistence Via MyComputer Registry Keys ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects modification to the "Default" value of the "MyComputer" key and subkeys to point to a custom binary that will be launched whenever the associated action is executed (see reference section for 
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Explorer\\MyComputer*" ObjectName="*(Default)"

# ── Potential Persistence Via DLLPathOverride ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects when an attacker adds a new "DLLPathOverride" value to the "Natural Language" key in order to achieve persistence which will get invoked by "SearchIndexer.exe" process
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\ContentIndex\\Language\\*" ObjectName IN ("*\\StemmerDLLPathOverride*", "*\\WBDLLPathOverride*", "*\\StemmerClass*", "*\\WBreakerClass*")

# ── Potential Persistence Via Visual Studio Tools for Office ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Chi tiết: Detects persistence via Visual Studio Tools for Office (VSTO) add-ins in Office applications.
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName IN ("*\\Software\\Microsoft\\Office\\Outlook\\Addins\\*", "*\\Software\\Microsoft\\Office\\Word\\Addins\\*", "*\\Software\\Microsoft\\Office\\Excel\\Addins\\*", "*\\Software\\Microsoft\\Office\\Powerpoint\\Addins\\*", "*\\Software\\Microsoft\\VSTO\\Security\\Inclusion\\*") NOT (ProcessName IN ("C:\\Windows\\System32\\msiexec.exe", "C:\\Windows\\SysWOW64\\msiexec.exe", "C:\\Windows\\System32\\regsvr32.exe", "C:\\Windows\\SysWOW64\\regsvr32.exe") OR (ProcessName IN ("C:\\Program Files\\Common Files (x86)\\Microsoft Shared\\ClickToRun\\*", "C:\\Program Files\\Common Files\\Microsoft Shared\\ClickToRun\\*") ProcessName="*\\OfficeClickToRun.exe") OR ProcessName IN ("C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Microsoft Office\\root\\integration\\integrator.exe", "C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft Office\\root\\integration\\integrator.exe") OR (ProcessName IN ("C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft Office\\OFFICE*", "C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Microsoft Office\\OFFICE*", "C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft Office\\Root\\OFFICE*", "C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Microsoft Office\\Root\\OFFICE*", "C:\\PROGRA~2\\MICROS~2\\Office*") ProcessName IN ("*\\excel.exe", "*\\Integrator.exe", "*\\OneNote.exe", "*\\outlook.exe", "*\\powerpnt.exe", "*\\Teams.exe", "*\\visio.exe", "*\\winword.exe")) OR (ProcessName IN ("C:\\Program Files\\Common Files\\Microsoft Shared\\VSTO\\*", "C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Microsoft Shared\\VSTO\\*") ProcessName="*\\VSTOInstaller.exe")) NOT ((ProcessName IN ("C:\\Program Files\\AVG\\Antivirus\\RegSvr.exe", "C:\\Program Files (x86)\\AVG\\Antivirus\\RegSvr.exe") ObjectName="*\\Microsoft\\Office\\Outlook\\Addins\\Antivirus.AsOutExt\\*") OR (ProcessName IN ("C:\\Program Files\\Avast Software\\Avast\\RegSvr.exe", "C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Avast Software\\Avast\\RegSvr.exe") ObjectName="*\\Microsoft\\Office\\Outlook\\Addins\\Avast.AsOutExt\\*"))

# ── Potential Persistence Via Outlook Home Page ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Mục đích: Sửa registry
# Chi tiết: Detects potential persistence activity via outlook home page. An attacker can set a home page to achieve code execution and persistence by editing the WebView registry keys.
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Software\\Microsoft\\Office\\*" ObjectName="*\\Outlook\\WebView\\*" ObjectName="*\\URL"

# ── Potential Persistence Via Outlook Today Page ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Mục đích: Sửa registry
# Chi tiết: Detects potential persistence activity via outlook today page. An attacker can set a custom page to execute arbitrary code and link to it via the registry values "URL" and "UserDefinedUrl".
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*Software\\Microsoft\\Office\\*" ObjectName="*\\Outlook\\Today\\*" (ObjectName="*\\Stamp" NewValue="DWORD (0x00000001)") OR ObjectName IN ("*\\URL", "*\\UserDefinedUrl") NOT (ProcessName IN ("C:\\Program Files\\Common Files\\Microsoft Shared\\ClickToRun\\*", "C:\\Program Files\\Common Files\\Microsoft Shared\\ClickToRun\\Updates\\*") ProcessName="*\\OfficeClickToRun.exe")

# ── Potential WerFault ReflectDebugger Registry Value Abuse ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Mục đích: Giả mạo tên tiến trình
# Chi tiết: Detects potential WerFault "ReflectDebugger" registry value abuse for persistence.
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Windows Error Reporting\\Hangs\\ReflectDebugger"

# ── Potential Persistence Via Scrobj.dll COM Hijacking ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Chi tiết: Detect use of scrobj.dll as this DLL looks for the ScriptletURL key to get the location of the script to execute
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*InprocServer32\\(Default)" NewValue="C:\\WINDOWS\\system32\\scrobj.dll"

# ── Potential Persistence Via Shim Database Modification ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Chi tiết: Adversaries may establish persistence and/or elevate privileges by executing malicious content triggered by application shims. The Microsoft Windows Application Compatibility Infrastructure/Framework 
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName IN ("*\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\AppCompatFlags\\InstalledSDB\\*", "*\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\AppCompatFlags\\Custom\\*") NOT (NewValue="" OR NewValue="(Empty)" OR NOT NewValue=*)

# ── Suspicious Shim Database Patching Activity ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects installation of new shim databases that try to patch sections of known processes for potential process injection or persistence.
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\AppCompatFlags\\Custom\\*" ObjectName IN ("*\\csrss.exe", "*\\dllhost.exe", "*\\explorer.exe", "*\\RuntimeBroker.exe", "*\\services.exe", "*\\sihost.exe", "*\\svchost.exe", "*\\taskhostw.exe", "*\\winlogon.exe", "*\\WmiPrvSe.exe")

# ── Potential Persistence Via Shim Database In Uncommon Location ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects the installation of a new shim database where the file is located in a non-default location
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\AppCompatFlags\\InstalledSDB\\*" ObjectName="*\\DatabasePath*" NOT NewValue="*:\\Windows\\AppPatch\\Custom*"

# ── Potential Persistence Via TypedPaths ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects modification addition to the 'TypedPaths' key in the user or admin registry from a non standard application. Which might indicate persistence attempt
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Explorer\\TypedPaths\\*" NOT (ProcessName IN ("C:\\Windows\\explorer.exe", "C:\\Windows\\SysWOW64\\explorer.exe"))

# ── Potential Persistence Via Excel Add-in - Registry ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detect potential persistence via the creation of an excel add-in (XLL) file to make it run automatically when Excel is started.
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*Software\\Microsoft\\Office\\*" ObjectName="*\\Excel\\Options" NewValue="/R *" NewValue="*.xll"

# ── Potential Attachment Manager Settings Associations Tamper ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects tampering with attachment manager settings policies associations to lower the default file type risks (See reference for more information)
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Associations\\*" (ObjectName="*\\DefaultFileTypeRisk" NewValue="DWORD (0x00006152)") OR (ObjectName="*\\LowRiskFileTypes" NewValue IN ("*.zip;*", "*.rar;*", "*.exe;*", "*.bat;*", "*.com;*", "*.cmd;*", "*.reg;*", "*.msi;*", "*.htm;*", "*.html;*"))

# ── Potential Attachment Manager Settings Attachments Tamper ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects tampering with attachment manager settings policies attachments (See reference for more information)
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Attachments\\*" (ObjectName="*\\HideZoneInfoOnProperties" NewValue="DWORD (0x00000001)") OR (ObjectName="*\\SaveZoneInformation" NewValue="DWORD (0x00000002)") OR (ObjectName="*\\ScanWithAntiVirus" NewValue="DWORD (0x00000001)")

# ── Potential ClickFix Execution Pattern - Registry ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects potential ClickFix malware execution patterns by monitoring registry modifications in RunMRU keys containing HTTP/HTTPS links. ClickFix is known to be distributed through phishing campaigns an
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Explorer\\RunMRU\\*" NewValue IN ("*http://*", "*https://*") NewValue IN ("*account*", "*anti-bot*", "*botcheck*", "*captcha*", "*challenge*", "*confirmation*", "*fraud*", "*human*", "*identification*", "*identificator*", "*identity*", "*robot*", "*validation*", "*verification*", "*verify*") OR NewValue IN ("*%comspec%*", "*bitsadmin*", "*certutil*", "*cmd*", "*cscript*", "*curl*", "*finger*", "*mshta*", "*powershell*", "*pwsh*", "*regsvr32*", "*rundll32*", "*schtasks*", "*wget*", "*wscript*")

# ── Registry Modification for OCI DLL Redirection ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Mục đích: Sửa registry
# Chi tiết: Detects registry modifications related to 'OracleOciLib' and 'OracleOciLibPath' under 'MSDTC' settings. Threat actors may modify these registry keys to redirect the loading of 'oci.dll' to a malicious
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" (ObjectName="*\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\MSDTC\\MTxOCI\\OracleOciLib" NOT NewValue="*oci.dll*") OR (ObjectName="*\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\MSDTC\\MTxOCI\\OracleOciLibPath" NOT NewValue="*%SystemRoot%\\System32\\*")

# ── PowerShell as a Service in Registry ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects that a powershell code is written to the registry as a service.
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Services\\*" ObjectName="*\\ImagePath" NewValue IN ("*powershell*", "*pwsh*")

# ── PowerShell Script Execution Policy Enabled ──
# Mức độ  : Thấp
# Chi tiết: Detects the enabling of the PowerShell script execution policy. Once enabled, this policy allows scripts to be executed.
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\PowerShell\\EnableScripts" NewValue="DWORD (0x00000001)"

# ── Potential PowerShell Execution Policy Tampering ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Chi tiết: Detects changes to the PowerShell execution policy in order to bypass signing requirements for script execution
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName IN ("*\\ShellIds\\Microsoft.PowerShell\\ExecutionPolicy", "*\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\PowerShell\\ExecutionPolicy") NewValue IN ("*Bypass*", "*Unrestricted*") NOT (ProcessName IN ("*:\\Windows\\System32\\*", "*:\\Windows\\SysWOW64\\*"))

# ── Suspicious PowerShell In Registry Run Keys ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Mục đích: Persistence qua autorun
# Chi tiết: Detects potential PowerShell commands or code within registry run keys
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName IN ("*\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Run*", "*\\Software\\WOW6432Node\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Run*", "*\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\Run*") NewValue IN ("*powershell*", "*pwsh *", "*FromBase64String*", "*.DownloadFile(*", "*.DownloadString(*", "* -w hidden *", "* -w 1 *", "*-windowstyle hidden*", "*-window hidden*", "* -nop *", "* -encodedcommand *", "*-ExecutionPolicy Bypass*", "*Invoke-Expression*", "*IEX (*", "*Invoke-Command*", "*ICM -*", "*Invoke-WebRequest*", "*IWR *", "*Invoke-RestMethod*", "*IRM *", "* -noni *", "* -noninteractive *")

# ── PowerShell Logging Disabled Via Registry Key Tampering ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Mục đích: Sửa registry
# Chi tiết: Detects changes to the registry for the currently logged-in user. In order to disable PowerShell module logging, script block logging or transcription and script execution logging
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName IN ("*\\Microsoft\\Windows\\PowerShell\\*", "*\\Microsoft\\PowerShellCore\\*") ObjectName IN ("*\\ModuleLogging\\EnableModuleLogging", "*\\ScriptBlockLogging\\EnableScriptBlockLogging", "*\\ScriptBlockLogging\\EnableScriptBlockInvocationLogging", "*\\Transcription\\EnableTranscripting", "*\\Transcription\\EnableInvocationHeader", "*\\EnableScripts") NewValue="DWORD (0x00000000)"

# ── Potential Provisioning Registry Key Abuse For Binary Proxy Execution - REG ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects potential abuse of the provisioning registry key for indirect command execution through "Provlaunch.exe".
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Provisioning\\Commands\\*"

# ── PUA - Sysinternal Tool Execution - Registry ──
# Mức độ  : Thấp
# Chi tiết: Detects the execution of a Sysinternals Tool via the creation of the "accepteula" registry key
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\EulaAccepted"

# ── Suspicious Execution Of Renamed Sysinternals Tools - Registry ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects the creation of the "accepteula" key related to the Sysinternals tools being created from executables with the wrong name (e.g. a renamed Sysinternals tool)
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName IN ("*\\Active Directory Explorer*", "*\\Handle*", "*\\LiveKd*", "*\\ProcDump*", "*\\Process Explorer*", "*\\PsExec*", "*\\PsLoggedon*", "*\\PsLoglist*", "*\\PsPasswd*", "*\\PsPing*", "*\\PsService*", "*\\SDelete*") ObjectName="*\\EulaAccepted" NOT (ProcessName IN ("*\\ADExplorer.exe", "*\\ADExplorer64.exe", "*\\ADExplorer64a.exe", "*\\handle.exe", "*\\handle64.exe", "*\\handle64a.exe", "*\\livekd.exe", "*\\livekd64.exe", "*\\procdump.exe", "*\\procdump64.exe", "*\\procdump64a.exe", "*\\procexp.exe", "*\\procexp64.exe", "*\\procexp64a.exe", "*\\PsExec.exe", "*\\PsExec64.exe", "*\\PsExec64a.exe", "*\\PsLoggedon.exe", "*\\PsLoggedon64.exe", "*\\psloglist.exe", "*\\psloglist64.exe", "*\\psloglist64a.exe", "*\\pspasswd.exe", "*\\pspasswd64.exe", "*\\pspasswd64a.exe", "*\\PsPing.exe", "*\\PsPing64.exe", "*\\PsPing64a.exe", "*\\PsService.exe", "*\\PsService64.exe", "*\\PsService64a.exe", "*\\sdelete.exe"))

# ── PUA - Sysinternals Tools Execution - Registry ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Chi tiết: Detects the execution of some potentially unwanted tools such as PsExec, Procdump, etc. (part of the Sysinternals suite) via the creation of the "accepteula" registry key.
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName IN ("*\\Active Directory Explorer*", "*\\Handle*", "*\\LiveKd*", "*\\Process Explorer*", "*\\ProcDump*", "*\\PsExec*", "*\\PsLoglist*", "*\\PsPasswd*", "*\\SDelete*", "*\\Sysinternals*") ObjectName="*\\EulaAccepted"

# ── Usage of Renamed Sysinternals Tools - RegistrySet ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects non-sysinternals tools setting the "accepteula" key which normally is set on sysinternals tool execution
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName IN ("*\\PsExec*", "*\\ProcDump*", "*\\Handle*", "*\\LiveKd*", "*\\Process Explorer*", "*\\PsLoglist*", "*\\PsPasswd*", "*\\Active Directory Explorer*") ObjectName="*\\EulaAccepted" NOT (ProcessName IN ("*\\PsExec.exe", "*\\PsExec64.exe", "*\\PsExec64a.exe", "*\\procdump.exe", "*\\procdump64.exe", "*\\procdump64a.exe", "*\\handle.exe", "*\\handle64.exe", "*\\handle64a.exe", "*\\livekd.exe", "*\\livekd64.exe", "*\\procexp.exe", "*\\procexp64.exe", "*\\procexp64a.exe", "*\\psloglist.exe", "*\\psloglist64.exe", "*\\psloglist64a.exe", "*\\pspasswd.exe", "*\\pspasswd64.exe", "*\\pspasswd64a.exe", "*\\ADExplorer.exe", "*\\ADExplorer64.exe", "*\\ADExplorer64a.exe")) NOT NOT ProcessName=*

# ── ETW Logging Disabled For rpcrt4.dll ──
# Mức độ  : Thấp
# Mục đích: Sửa registry
# Chi tiết: Detects changes to the "ExtErrorInformation" key in order to disable ETW logging for rpcrt4.dll
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Rpc\\ExtErrorInformation" NewValue IN ("DWORD (0x00000000)", "DWORD (0x00000002)")

# ── Potentially Suspicious Command Executed Via Run Dialog Box - Registry ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Mục đích: Thực thi lệnh/script
# Chi tiết: Detects execution of commands via the run dialog box on Windows by checking values of the "RunMRU" registry key. This technique was seen being abused by threat actors to deceive users into pasting and
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Explorer\\RunMRU*" (NewValue IN ("*powershell*", "*pwsh*") NewValue IN ("* -e *", "* -ec *", "* -en *", "* -enc *", "* -enco*", "*ftp*", "*Hidden*", "*http*", "*iex*", "*Invoke-*")) OR (NewValue="*wmic*" NewValue IN ("*shadowcopy*", "*process call create*"))

# ── ScreenSaver Registry Key Set ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Chi tiết: Detects registry key established after masqueraded .scr file execution using Rundll32 through desk.cpl
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ProcessName="*\\rundll32.exe" ObjectName="*\\Control Panel\\Desktop\\SCRNSAVE.EXE*" NewValue="*.scr" NOT (NewValue IN ("*C:\\Windows\\System32\\*", "*C:\\Windows\\SysWOW64\\*"))

# ── Potential SentinelOne Shell Context Menu Scan Command Tampering ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Chi tiết: Detects potentially suspicious changes to the SentinelOne context menu scan command by a process other than SentinelOne.
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\shell\\SentinelOneScan\\command\\*" NOT ((NewValue IN ("C:\\Program Files\\SentinelOne\\Sentinel Agent*", "C:\\Program Files (x86)\\SentinelOne\\Sentinel Agent*") NewValue="*\\SentinelScanFromContextMenu.exe*") OR ProcessName IN ("*C:\\Program Files\\SentinelOne\\", "*C:\\Program Files (x86)\\SentinelOne\\"))

# ── ServiceDll Hijack ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Chi tiết: Detects changes to the "ServiceDLL" value related to a service in the registry. This is often used as a method of persistence.
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\System\\*" ObjectName="*ControlSet*" ObjectName="*\\Services\\*" ObjectName="*\\Parameters\\ServiceDll" NOT (NewValue="C:\\Windows\\system32\\spool\\drivers\\x64\\3\\PrintConfig.dll" OR (ProcessName="C:\\Windows\\system32\\lsass.exe" ObjectName="*\\Services\\NTDS\\Parameters\\ServiceDll" NewValue="%%systemroot%%\\system32\\ntdsa.dll") OR ProcessName="C:\\Windows\\System32\\poqexec.exe") NOT (ProcessName="*\\regsvr32.exe" NewValue="C:\\Windows\\System32\\STAgent.dll")

# ── ETW Logging Disabled For SCM ──
# Mức độ  : Thấp
# Mục đích: Sửa registry
# Chi tiết: Detects changes to the "TracingDisabled" key in order to disable ETW logging for services.exe (SCM)
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*Software\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Tracing\\SCM\\Regular\\TracingDisabled" NewValue="DWORD (0x00000001)"

# ── Registry Explorer Policy Modification ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Mục đích: Sửa registry
# Chi tiết: Detects registry modifications that disable internal tools or functions in explorer (malware like Agent Tesla uses this technique)
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName IN ("*SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\NoLogOff", "*SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\NoDesktop", "*SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\NoRun", "*SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\NoFind", "*SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\NoControlPanel", "*SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\NoFileMenu", "*SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\NoClose", "*SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\NoSetTaskbar", "*SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\NoPropertiesMyDocuments", "*SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\NoTrayContextMenu") NewValue="DWORD (0x00000001)"

# ── Persistence Via New SIP Provider ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Chi tiết: Detects when an attacker register a new SIP provider for persistence and defense evasion
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName IN ("*\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Cryptography\\Providers\\*", "*\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Cryptography\\OID\\EncodingType*", "*\\SOFTWARE\\WOW6432Node\\Microsoft\\Cryptography\\Providers\\*", "*\\SOFTWARE\\WOW6432Node\\Microsoft\\Cryptography\\OID\\EncodingType*") ObjectName IN ("*\\Dll*", "*\\$DLL*") NOT (NewValue IN ("WINTRUST.DLL", "mso.dll") OR (ProcessName="C:\\Windows\\System32\\poqexec.exe" ObjectName="*\\CryptSIPDll*" NewValue="C:\\Windows\\System32\\PsfSip.dll"))

# ── Tamper With Sophos AV Registry Keys ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects tamper attempts to sophos av functionality via registry key modification
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName IN ("*\\Sophos Endpoint Defense\\TamperProtection\\Config\\SAVEnabled*", "*\\Sophos Endpoint Defense\\TamperProtection\\Config\\SEDEnabled*", "*\\Sophos\\SAVService\\TamperProtection\\Enabled*") NewValue="DWORD (0x00000000)"

# ── Hiding User Account Via SpecialAccounts Registry Key ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects modifications to the registry key "HKLM\Software\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Winlogon\SpecialAccounts\Userlist" where the value is set to "0" in order to hide user account from being l
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\SpecialAccounts\\UserList*" NewValue="DWORD (0x00000000)"

# ── Activate Suppression of Windows Security Center Notifications ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Mục đích: Sửa registry
# Chi tiết: Detect set Notification_Suppress to 1 to disable the Windows security center notification
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\UX Configuration\\Notification_Suppress" NewValue="DWORD (0x00000001)"

# ── Suspicious Keyboard Layout Load ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Chi tiết: Detects the keyboard preload installation with a suspicious keyboard layout, e.g. Chinese, Iranian or Vietnamese layout load in user session on systems maintained by US staff only
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName IN ("*\\Keyboard Layout\\Preload\\*", "*\\Keyboard Layout\\Substitutes\\*") NewValue IN ("*00000429*", "*00050429*", "*0000042a*")

# ── Potential PendingFileRenameOperations Tampering ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Mục đích: Giả mạo tên tiến trình
# Chi tiết: Detect changes to the "PendingFileRenameOperations" registry key from uncommon or suspicious images locations to stage currently used files for rename or deletion after reboot.
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\\PendingFileRenameOperations*" ProcessName="*\\Users\\Public\\*" OR ProcessName IN ("*\\reg.exe", "*\\regedit.exe")

# ── Suspicious Printer Driver Empty Manufacturer ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects a suspicious printer driver installation with an empty Manufacturer value
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Control\\Print\\Environments\\Windows x64\\Drivers*" ObjectName="*\\Manufacturer*" NewValue="(Empty)" NOT (ObjectName="*\\CutePDF Writer v4.0\\*" OR ObjectName IN ("*\\VNC Printer (PS)\\*", "*\\VNC Printer (UD)\\*") OR ObjectName="*\\Version-3\\PDF24\\*")

# ── Registry Persistence via Explorer Run Key ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Mục đích: Persistence qua autorun
# Chi tiết: Detects a possible persistence mechanism using RUN key for Windows Explorer and pointing to a suspicious folder
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\Run" NewValue IN ("*:\\$Recycle.bin\\*", "*:\\ProgramData\\*", "*:\\Temp\\*", "*:\\Users\\Default\\*", "*:\\Users\\Public\\*", "*:\\Windows\\Temp\\*", "*\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\*")

# ── New RUN Key Pointing to Suspicious Folder ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Mục đích: Persistence qua autorun
# Chi tiết: Detects suspicious new RUN key element pointing to an executable in a suspicious folder
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName IN ("*\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Run*", "*\\Software\\WOW6432Node\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Run*", "*\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\Run*") NewValue IN ("*:\\Perflogs*", "*:\\ProgramData'*", "*:\\Windows\\Temp*", "*:\\Temp*", "*\\AppData\\Local\\Temp*", "*\\AppData\\Roaming*", "*:\\$Recycle.bin*", "*:\\Users\\Default*", "*:\\Users\\public*", "*%temp%*", "*%tmp%*", "*%Public%*", "*%AppData%*") OR (NewValue="*:\\Users\\*" NewValue IN ("*\\Favorites*", "*\\Favourites*", "*\\Contacts*", "*\\Music*", "*\\Pictures*", "*\\Documents*", "*\\Photos*")) NOT (ObjectName="*\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\RunOnce\\*" ProcessName="C:\\Windows\\SoftwareDistribution\\Download\\*" NewValue="*rundll32.exe *" NewValue="*C:\\WINDOWS\\system32\\advpack.dll,DelNodeRunDLL32*" NewValue IN ("*\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\*", "*C:\\Windows\\Temp\\*")) NOT (ProcessName IN ("*C:\\Program Files\\Spotify\\Spotify.exe", "*C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Spotify\\Spotify.exe", "*\\AppData\\Roaming\\Spotify\\Spotify.exe") ObjectName="*SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Run\\Spotify" NewValue="*Spotify.exe --autostart --minimized")

# ── Suspicious Space Characters in RunMRU Registry Path - ClickFix ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects the occurrence of numerous space characters in RunMRU registry paths, which may indicate execution via phishing lures using clickfix techniques to hide malicious commands in the Windows Run di
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Explorer\\RunMRU\\*" NewValue="*#*" NewValue IN ("*            *", "*            *", "*            *", "*            *", "*            *", "*            *", "*            *", "*            *", "*            *", "*            *", "*            *", "*            *", "*            *")

# ── Suspicious Service Installed ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Chi tiết: Detects installation of NalDrv or PROCEXP152 services via registry-keys to non-system32 folders. Both services are used in the tool Ghost-In-The-Logs (https://github.com/bats3c/Ghost-In-The-Logs), whi
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName IN ("\\REGISTRY\\MACHINE\\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\NalDrv\\ImagePath", "\\REGISTRY\\MACHINE\\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\PROCEXP152\\ImagePath") NOT (ProcessName IN ("*\\procexp64.exe", "*\\procexp64a.exe", "*\\procexp.exe", "*\\procmon64.exe", "*\\procmon64a.exe", "*\\procmon.exe", "*\\handle.exe", "*\\handle64.exe", "*\\handle64a.exe") NewValue="*\\WINDOWS\\system32\\Drivers\\PROCEXP152.SYS*")

# ── Suspicious Shell Open Command Registry Modification ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Mục đích: Leo thang đặc quyền
# Chi tiết: Detects modifications to shell open registry keys that point to suspicious locations typically used by malware for persistence. Generally, modifications to the `*\shell\open\command` registry key can 
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\shell\\open\\command\\*" NewValue IN ("*\\$Recycle.Bin\\*", "*\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\*", "*\\Contacts\\*", "*\\Music\\*", "*\\PerfLogs\\*", "*\\Photos\\*", "*\\Pictures\\*", "*\\Users\\Public\\*", "*\\Videos\\*", "*\\Windows\\Temp\\*", "*%AppData%*", "*%LocalAppData%*", "*%Temp%*", "*%tmp%*")

# ── Suspicious Space Characters in TypedPaths Registry Path - FileFix ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects the occurrence of numerous space characters in TypedPaths registry paths, which may indicate execution via phishing lures using file-fix techniques to hide malicious commands.
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Explorer\\TypedPaths\\url1" NewValue="*#*" NewValue IN ("*            *", "*            *", "*            *", "*            *", "*            *", "*            *", "*            *", "*            *", "*            *", "*            *", "*            *", "*            *", "*            *")

# ── Modify User Shell Folders Startup Value ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Mục đích: Persistence qua autorun
# Chi tiết: Detect modification of the User Shell Folders registry values for Startup or Common Startup which could indicate persistence attempts. Attackers may modify User Shell Folders registry keys to point to
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName IN ("*SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Explorer\\User Shell Folders*", "*SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Explorer\\Shell Folders*") ObjectName IN ("*\\Common Startup", "*\\Startup") NOT (NOT NewValue=* OR NewValue IN ("*C:\\ProgramData\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Start Menu\\Programs\\Startup*", "*%ProgramData%\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Start Menu\\Programs\\Startup*") OR NewValue IN ("*%USERPROFILE%\\AppData\\Roaming\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Start Menu\\Programs\\Startup*", "*%%USERPROFILE%%\\AppData\\Roaming\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Start Menu\\Programs\\Startup*") OR (NewValue="*C:\\Users\\*" NewValue="*\\AppData\\Roaming\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Start Menu\\Programs\\Startup*"))

# ── WFP Filter Added via Registry ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Chi tiết: Detects registry modifications that add Windows Filtering Platform (WFP) filters, which may be used to block security tools and EDR agents from reporting events.
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\BFE\\Parameters\\Policy\\Persistent\\Filter\\*" NOT (ProcessName IN ("C:\\Windows\\System32\\svchost.exe", "C:\\Windows\\SysWOW64\\svchost.exe"))

# ── Suspicious Environment Variable Has Been Registered ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects the creation of user-specific or system-wide environment variables via the registry. Which contains suspicious commands and strings
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Environment\\*" NewValue IN ("powershell", "pwsh") OR NewValue IN ("*\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\*", "*C:\\Users\\Public\\*", "*TVqQAAMAAAAEAAAA*", "*TVpQAAIAAAAEAA8A*", "*TVqAAAEAAAAEABAA*", "*TVoAAAAAAAAAAAAA*", "*TVpTAQEAAAAEAAAA*", "*SW52b2tlL*", "*ludm9rZS*", "*JbnZva2Ut*", "*SQBuAHYAbwBrAGUALQ*", "*kAbgB2AG8AawBlAC0A*", "*JAG4AdgBvAGsAZQAtA*") OR NewValue IN ("SUVY*", "SQBFAF*", "SQBuAH*", "cwBhA*", "aWV4*", "aQBlA*", "R2V0*", "dmFy*", "dgBhA*", "dXNpbm*", "H4sIA*", "Y21k*", "cABhAH*", "Qzpc*", "Yzpc*")

# ── Enable LM Hash Storage ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Mục đích: Sửa registry
# Chi tiết: Detects changes to the "NoLMHash" registry value in order to allow Windows to store LM Hashes. By setting this registry value to "0" (DWORD), Windows will be allowed to store a LAN manager hash of you
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\NoLMHash" NewValue="DWORD (0x00000000)"

# ── Scheduled TaskCache Change by Uncommon Program ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Mục đích: Lên lịch tác vụ độc hại
# Chi tiết: Monitor the creation of a new key under 'TaskCache' when a new scheduled task is registered by a process that is not svchost.exe, which is suspicious
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Schedule\\TaskCache\\*" NOT (NewValue="(Empty)" OR NOT NewValue=* OR ObjectName IN ("*Microsoft\\Windows\\UpdateOrchestrator*", "*Microsoft\\Windows\\SoftwareProtectionPlatform\\SvcRestartTask\\Index*", "*Microsoft\\Windows\\Flighting\\OneSettings\\RefreshCache\\Index*") OR ProcessName="*C:\\Windows\\System32\\MoUsoCoreWorker.exe" OR ProcessName="*C:\\Windows\\System32\\services.exe" OR (ProcessName="C:\\Windows\\*" ProcessName="*\\TiWorker.exe") OR ProcessName="C:\\WINDOWS\\system32\\svchost.exe" OR (ProcessName="C:\\Windows\\Microsoft.NET\\Framework*" ProcessName="*\\ngen.exe" ObjectName IN ("*\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Schedule\\TaskCache\\Tasks\\{B66B135D-DA06-4FC4-95F8-7458E1D10129}*", "*\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Schedule\\TaskCache\\Tree\\Microsoft\\Windows\\.NET Framework\\.NET Framework NGEN*")) OR ProcessName IN ("C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft Office\\root\\Integration\\Integrator.exe", "C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Microsoft Office\\root\\Integration\\Integrator.exe", "C:\\Program Files\\Common Files\\microsoft shared\\ClickToRun\\OfficeC2RClient.exe", "C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Common Files\\microsoft shared\\ClickToRun\\OfficeC2RClient.exe") OR ProcessName="C:\\Windows\\System32\\msiexec.exe" OR (ProcessName="C:\\Windows\\explorer.exe" ObjectName="*\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Schedule\\TaskCache\\Tree\\Microsoft\\Windows\\PLA\\Server Manager Performance Monitor\\*") OR ProcessName="System" OR ProcessName="C:\\Windows\\System32\\RuntimeBroker.exe") NOT (ProcessName IN ("C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Dropbox\\Update\\DropboxUpdate.exe", "C:\\Program Files\\Dropbox\\Update\\DropboxUpdate.exe") OR ProcessName IN ("*C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Microsoft\\EdgeUpdate\\MicrosoftEdgeUpdate.exe", "*C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft\\EdgeUpdate\\MicrosoftEdgeUpdate.exe") OR ProcessName IN ("*C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Microsoft OneDrive\\OneDrive.exe", "*C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft OneDrive\\OneDrive.exe"))

# ── Potential Registry Persistence Attempt Via Windows Telemetry ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Mục đích: Lên lịch tác vụ độc hại
# Chi tiết: Detects potential persistence behavior using the windows telemetry registry key. Windows telemetry makes use of the binary CompatTelRunner.exe to run a variety of commands and perform the actual telem
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\AppCompatFlags\\TelemetryController\\*" ObjectName="*\\Command" NewValue IN ("*.bat*", "*.bin*", "*.cmd*", "*.dat*", "*.dll*", "*.exe*", "*.hta*", "*.jar*", "*.js*", "*.msi*", "*.ps*", "*.sh*", "*.vb*") NOT (NewValue IN ("*\\system32\\CompatTelRunner.exe*", "*\\system32\\DeviceCensus.exe*"))

# ── RDP Sensitive Settings Changed to Zero ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Mục đích: Sửa registry
# Chi tiết: Detects tampering of RDP Terminal Service/Server sensitive settings. Such as allowing unauthorized users access to a system via the 'fAllowUnsolicited' or enabling RDP via 'fDenyTSConnections', etc.
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName IN ("*\\fDenyTSConnections", "*\\fSingleSessionPerUser", "*\\UserAuthentication") NewValue="DWORD (0x00000000)"

# ── RDP Sensitive Settings Changed ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Mục đích: Sửa registry
# Chi tiết: Detects tampering of RDP Terminal Service/Server sensitive settings. Such as allowing unauthorized users access to a system via the 'fAllowUnsolicited' or enabling RDP via 'fDenyTSConnections', etc.  
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" (ObjectName IN ("*\\Control\\Terminal Server\\*", "*\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\*") ObjectName="*\\Shadow" NewValue IN ("DWORD (0x00000001)", "DWORD (0x00000002)", "DWORD (0x00000003)", "DWORD (0x00000004)")) OR (ObjectName IN ("*\\Control\\Terminal Server\\*", "*\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\*") ObjectName IN ("*\\DisableRemoteDesktopAntiAlias", "*\\DisableSecuritySettings", "*\\fAllowUnsolicited", "*\\fAllowUnsolicitedFullControl") NewValue="DWORD (0x00000001)") OR ObjectName IN ("*\\Control\\Terminal Server\\InitialProgram*", "*\\Control\\Terminal Server\\WinStations\\RDP-Tcp\\InitialProgram*", "*\\services\\TermService\\Parameters\\ServiceDll*", "*\\Terminal Server\\WinStations\\RDP-Tcp\\SecurityLayer*", "*\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\InitialProgram*") NOT (ObjectName="*\\SecurityLayer" NewValue="DWORD (0x00000002)")

# ── New TimeProviders Registered With Uncommon DLL Name ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Mục đích: Persistence qua autorun
# Chi tiết: Detects processes setting a new DLL in DllName in under HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\W32Time\TimeProvider. Adversaries may abuse time providers to execute DLLs when the system 
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Services\\W32Time\\TimeProviders*" ObjectName="*\\DllName" NOT (NewValue IN ("%SystemRoot%\\System32\\vmictimeprovider.dll", "%systemroot%\\system32\\w32time.dll", "C:\\Windows\\SYSTEM32\\w32time.DLL"))

# ── Old TLS1.0/TLS1.1 Protocol Version Enabled ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Chi tiết: Detects applications or users re-enabling old TLS versions by setting the "Enabled" value to "1" for the "Protocols" registry key.
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName IN ("*\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\TLS 1.0\\*", "*\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\TLS 1.1\\*") ObjectName="*\\Enabled" NewValue="DWORD (0x00000001)"

# ── COM Hijacking via TreatAs ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Chi tiết: Detect modification of TreatAs key to enable "rundll32.exe -sta" command
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*TreatAs\\(Default)" NOT ((ProcessName="C:\\Program Files\\Common Files\\Microsoft Shared\\ClickToRun\\*" ProcessName="*\\OfficeClickToRun.exe") OR ProcessName IN ("C:\\Program Files\\Microsoft Office\\root\\integration\\integrator.exe", "C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Microsoft Office\\root\\integration\\integrator.exe") OR ProcessName="C:\\Windows\\system32\\svchost.exe" OR ProcessName IN ("C:\\Windows\\system32\\msiexec.exe", "C:\\Windows\\SysWOW64\\msiexec.exe"))

# ── Potential Signing Bypass Via Windows Developer Features - Registry ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects when the enablement of developer features such as "Developer Mode" or "Application Sideloading". Which allows the user to install untrusted packages.
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName IN ("*\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\AppModelUnlock*", "*\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Appx\\*") ObjectName IN ("*\\AllowAllTrustedApps", "*\\AllowDevelopmentWithoutDevLicense") NewValue="DWORD (0x00000001)"

# ── UAC Bypass via Event Viewer ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Mục đích: Leo thang đặc quyền
# Chi tiết: Detects UAC bypass method using Windows event viewer
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\mscfile\\shell\\open\\command"

# ── UAC Bypass via Sdclt ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Mục đích: Leo thang đặc quyền
# Chi tiết: Detects the pattern of UAC Bypass using registry key manipulation of sdclt.exe (e.g. UACMe 53)
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*Software\\Classes\\exefile\\shell\\runas\\command\\isolatedCommand"
| rex field=NewValue "(?<NewValueMatch>-1[0-9]{3}\\\\Software\\\\Classes\\\\)"
| eval NewValueCondition=if(isnotnull(NewValueMatch), "true", "false")
| search OR (ObjectName="*Software\\Classes\\Folder\\shell\\open\\command\\SymbolicLinkValue" NewValueCondition="true")

# ── UAC Bypass Abusing Winsat Path Parsing - Registry ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Mục đích: Leo thang đặc quyền
# Chi tiết: Detects the pattern of UAC Bypass using a path parsing issue in winsat.exe (UACMe 52)
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Root\\InventoryApplicationFile\\winsat.exe|*" ObjectName="*\\LowerCaseLongPath" NewValue="c:\\users\\*" NewValue="*\\appdata\\local\\temp\\system32\\winsat.exe"

# ── UAC Bypass Using Windows Media Player - Registry ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Mục đích: Leo thang đặc quyền
# Chi tiết: Detects the pattern of UAC Bypass using Windows Media Player osksupport.dll (UACMe 32)
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\AppCompatFlags\\Compatibility Assistant\\Store\\C:\\Program Files\\Windows Media Player\\osk.exe" NewValue="Binary Data"

# ── UAC Disabled ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Mục đích: Leo thang đặc quyền
# Chi tiết: Detects when an attacker tries to disable User Account Control (UAC) by setting the registry value "EnableLUA" to 0.
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\EnableLUA*" NewValue="DWORD (0x00000000)"

# ── UAC Notification Disabled ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Mục đích: Leo thang đặc quyền
# Chi tiết: Detects when an attacker tries to disable User Account Control (UAC) notification by tampering with the "UACDisableNotify" value. UAC is a critical security feature in Windows that prevents unauthoriz
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Microsoft\\Security Center\\UACDisableNotify*" NewValue="DWORD (0x00000001)"

# ── UAC Secure Desktop Prompt Disabled ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Mục đích: Leo thang đặc quyền
# Chi tiết: Detects when an attacker tries to change User Account Control (UAC) elevation request destination via the "PromptOnSecureDesktop" value. The "PromptOnSecureDesktop" setting specifically determines whe
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\PromptOnSecureDesktop*" NewValue="DWORD (0x00000000)"

# ── VBScript Payload Stored in Registry ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Mục đích: Persistence qua autorun
# Chi tiết: Detects VBScript content stored into registry keys as seen being used by UNC2452 group
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion*" NewValue IN ("*vbscript:*", "*jscript:*", "*mshtml,*", "*RunHTMLApplication*", "*Execute(*", "*CreateObject*", "*window.close*") NOT (ObjectName="*Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Run*" OR (ProcessName="*\\msiexec.exe" ObjectName="*\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Installer\\UserData\\*" NewValue IN ("*\\Microsoft.NET\\Primary Interop Assemblies\\Microsoft.mshtml.dll*", "*<\\Microsoft.mshtml,fileVersion=*", "*_mshtml_dll_*", "*<\\Microsoft.mshtml,culture=*")))

# ── Windows Vulnerable Driver Blocklist Disabled ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects when the Windows Vulnerable Driver Blocklist is set to disabled. This setting is crucial for preventing the loading of known vulnerable drivers, and its modification may indicate an attempt to
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Control\\CI\\Config\\VulnerableDriverBlocklistEnable" NewValue="DWORD (0x00000000)"

# ── Execution DLL of Choice Using WAB.EXE ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: This rule detects that the path to the DLL written in the registry is different from the default one. Launched WAB.exe tries to load the DLL from Registry.
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Software\\Microsoft\\WAB\\DLLPath" NOT NewValue="%CommonProgramFiles%\\System\\wab32.dll"

# ── Wdigest Enable UseLogonCredential ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Mục đích: Sửa registry
# Chi tiết: Detects potential malicious modification of the property value of UseLogonCredential from HKLM:\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\SecurityProviders\WDigest to enable clear-text credentials
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*WDigest\\UseLogonCredential" NewValue="DWORD (0x00000001)"

# ── Disable Windows Defender Functionalities Via Registry Keys ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Chi tiết: Detects when attackers or tools disable Windows Defender functionalities via the Windows registry
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName IN ("*\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\*", "*\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender Security Center\\*", "*\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\*") (ObjectName IN ("*\\DisableAntiSpyware", "*\\DisableAntiVirus", "*\\DisableBehaviorMonitoring", "*\\DisableBlockAtFirstSeen", "*\\DisableEnhancedNotifications", "*\\DisableIntrusionPreventionSystem", "*\\DisableIOAVProtection", "*\\DisableOnAccessProtection", "*\\DisableRealtimeMonitoring", "*\\DisableScanOnRealtimeEnable", "*\\DisableScriptScanning") NewValue="DWORD (0x00000001)") OR (ObjectName IN ("*\\DisallowExploitProtectionOverride", "*\\Features\\TamperProtection", "*\\MpEngine\\MpEnablePus", "*\\PUAProtection", "*\\Signature Update\\ForceUpdateFromMU", "*\\SpyNet\\SpynetReporting", "*\\SpyNet\\SubmitSamplesConsent", "*\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\Controlled Folder Access\\EnableControlledFolderAccess") NewValue="DWORD (0x00000000)") NOT (ProcessName="C:\\Program Files\\Symantec\\Symantec Endpoint Protection\\*" ProcessName="*\\sepWscSvc64.exe")

# ── Winget Admin Settings Modification ──
# Mức độ  : Thấp
# Chi tiết: Detects changes to the AppInstaller (winget) admin settings. Such as enabling local manifest installations or disabling installer hash checks
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ProcessName="*\\winget.exe" ObjectName="\\REGISTRY\\A\\*" ObjectName="*\\LocalState\\admin_settings"

# ── Enable Local Manifest Installation With Winget ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Chi tiết: Detects changes to the AppInstaller (winget) policy. Specifically the activation of the local manifest installation, which allows a user to install new packages via custom manifests.
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\AppInstaller\\EnableLocalManifestFiles" NewValue="DWORD (0x00000001)"

# ── Winlogon AllowMultipleTSSessions Enable ──
# Mức độ  : Trung bình
# Mục đích: Sửa registry
# Chi tiết: Detects when the 'AllowMultipleTSSessions' value is enabled. Which allows for multiple Remote Desktop connection sessions to be opened at once. This is often used by attacker as a way to connect to an
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\AllowMultipleTSSessions" NewValue="*DWORD (0x00000001)"

# ── Winlogon Notify Key Logon Persistence ──
# Mức độ  : Cao
# Mục đích: Persistence qua autorun
# Chi tiết: Adversaries may abuse features of Winlogon to execute DLLs and/or executables when a user logs in. Winlogon.exe is a Windows component responsible for actions at logon/logoff as well as the secure att
EventCode=4657 Channel="Security" ObjectName="*\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\Notify\\logon" NewValue="*.dll"
